				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Multi Level Mania" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Multi Level Mania is a game where you join a multi-level marketing company (totally different from a pyramid scheme, we swear!) and hustle your way to the top by pitching the products or the company to character cards. The goal of the game is to make $10,000 before the Cubicle Troll (an NPC with a regular paycheck) and before all the other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game can be played by 2-6 players and takes between 1-2 hours.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round consists of four phases: the Hustle phase, the Payday phase, the Restock phase, and the Event phase:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the Hustle phase, players choose character cards and roll a die to either try to sell product to that character, or to recruit that character as a downline.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the Payday phase, each player gets paid money according to the number and type of downlines they have - and the Cubicle Troll gets their paycheck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Next comes to Restock phase, when all players must buy at least the minimum required inventory to maintain membership in their chosen MLM - don't worry, you can take out credit cards if you need to!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Finally, during the event phase, each player selects an event card that can either help or hurt their chances of success. Then it's time for a new round with another Hustle phase!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game allows for some sabotage of other players by stealing or alienating their downlines, and all players have the opportunity to spend money to make money - just like a real pyramid scheme - I mean, multi-level marketing company!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
